article.headline: Austin Peay 92, Arkansas State 71
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Austin Peay jumped out to a 26-point lead in the first half and never trailed, coasting to a 92-71 win over Arkansas St. on Saturday night. Austin Peay (16-12) scored the first 12 points of the game, hitting 8-of-9 shots, and led 32-6 with 8:34 in the first half. The Governors scored 45 points off 22 Arkansas St. turnovers and shot 58 percent. Arkansas St. (12-15) grabbed 42 rebounds, while Austin Peay only pulled in 26. The Indians only shot 28 percent from the free-throw line in the second half after making all seven free throw attempts in the first half. Maurice Hampton sank 22 points for Austin Peay, and Derek Wright added 18. Zac Schlader scored 13, including his 1,000th career point with 1:04 left in the game. Isaac Wells netted 26 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for Arkansas St., and Marcus Ardison added 22 points and 10 rebounds. Yual Banks had 12 points.
